description:
Hi all!!!

My name is Jim and I'm the creator of this channel. This is my full time job and my mission is to bring you the highest quality and of high standard editing BeamNG drive videos with unique, meaningful and fun content.

BeamNG drive is the most realistic driving game that mimics every component of a vehicle in real time resulting in lifelike behavior.

All my videos are created by myself using the following programs : GeForce Experience for recording, Adobe Premiere Pro for editing and synchronizing the initially raw footage and Photoshop for thumbnails.

My weekly process consists of:
- Recording my clips ( 30 - 40 hours )
- Editing my clips ( 18 - 24 hours ) That includes editing in image, music, captions and sound effects.
-Thumbnails, description etc. roughly 10 hours.

I upload 3 times a week every Tuesday, Friday and Sunday, at 5pm GMT

Join me and be part of this adventure. 

Subscribe and stay tuned!

description:
Hello, I'm Andy. My goal is to create entertaining videos mostly, but not only, for people who love cars & crashes. 

All the videos you'll find in this channel are recorded & edited by me and my sidekick, George, who helps with parts of the editing.
This channel is our full-time job. We're devoting a minimum of 100 hours per week to bring you the best BeamNG drive videos.

How we work:

Creating these videos is a lot harder & time consuming than you might think but it is what makes us and, hopefully, you happy!
We are playing BeamNG.drive, a PC Game featuring the ultimate soft-body physics and realism. 

The process, step by step:

- Recording the clips with Action! (10-15 hours, sometimes 15+)
- Editing & synchronizing the clips with music & addition of captions / sound effects - Premiere Pro (5-10 hours)  
- Descriptions, Thumbnails etc.  (2 hours)

We’re uploading 4 Videos per week on Tuesday, Thursday, Saturday & Sunday. Stay up to date by Subscribing!
Thank you :)

description:
China Global Television Network, or CGTN, is an international media organization launched on December 31, 2016. It aims to provide global audiences with accurate and timely news coverage as well as rich audiovisual services, promoting communication and understanding between China and the world, and enhancing cultural exchanges and mutual trust between China and other countries. 

Headquartered in Beijing, CGTN has three production centers, located in Nairobi, Washington D.C. and London, all staffed with international professionals from around the world.

Adhering to the principles of objectivity, rationality and balance in reporting, CGTN endeavors to present information from diverse perspectives.

Effettuiamo i servizi di ordinaria e tradizionale officina e elettrauto:

-Cambio olio, Tagliandi
-Distribuzioni
-Frizioni
-Cambio freni
-Ammortizzatori
-Riparazioni meccaniche
-Riparazioni elettroniche
 

Parallelamente a ciò, il nostro fiore all’occhiello è la preparazione motoristica:

-Rimappatura ecu
-Scarichi sportivi
-Installazione di assetti sportivi
-Apertura del monoblocco con sostituzione Pistoni, Bielle e Bronzine
-Turbine e Intercooler maggiorati
-Kit di aspirazione

A tal fine è presente un’ampia sala motori e un banco prova potenza dinamometrico BAPRO (www.bapro.it) per certificare con trasparenza e professionalità i risultati ottenuti dai nostri sviluppi. 

Il sito: www.topspeedgarage.net
Pagina Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/topspeedgarageitaly/

Hello and welcome to my channel.


My name is Alex, and I'm a massive steam train enthusiast from Bristol. I film steam engines across the country, from filming steam on the mainline to preserved railways. I have plenty of new and exciting ideas lined up in the upcoming months and I still have plans for the future to come. With your support and dedication, we can make it happen. If you really like my channel and want to follow me, then why not click the SUBSCRIBE button for some exciting steam engines in action and let's help keep steam alive. Thank you very much for your time and effort.

description:
Hello! I'm Ayush Anand, and welcome to my YouTube channel. I have a passion for capturing the beauty and excitement of the railway world. Here, you'll find stunning train visuals, breathtaking scenery, and all things railway-related.

As I continue to grow and evolve as a content creator, I'm excited to expand my focus to include the many fascinating aspects of my environment. I want to share the impactful experiences and moments I encounter in my everyday life, offering you a glimpse into the world as I see and feel it.

While I have always been a shy person and kept my face off-camera, I'm stepping out of my comfort zone to connect with you more personally. Join me on this journey as I explore new horizons and share more of myself with all of you.

Thank you for being a part of this adventure. Don't forget to like, comment, and subscribe to stay updated with all my latest videos!

description:
As Foo fighters Dave Grohl said about the song Learn to fly: "It's about the search for some sort of inspiration, the search for signs of life that will make you feel alive." This sums up what happened to us, a couple of nerds who survived high school and learned to fly. Everything is a learning experience. No matter what is going on in your life, you dissect it, analyze it and learn from it.

We are interested in so many things and our channel reflects that. Travel, art, design, nature, animals, Disney.

We worked for Walt Disney World for over 20 years in a department called Artist Prep Support and then stepped away to have a little more control over our time and our artwork. We started up a creative business that sometimes does set design and theming. In our free time we create our own artwork from recycled materials and photos of our travel. 

I guess you could say we are just Nerds learning to fly.

Gatan is headquartered in Pleasanton, California, USA. For more information, visit www.gatan.com.

Gatan works with academic and industry researchers to push the boundaries of what can be done with electron microscopy. description:
Headed to the toughest job or your dream vacation spot? We are dedicated to getting you there. We're a group of gearheads, campers, fishermen, off-roaders, cyclists, mechanics, contractors, and landscapers who are here to do whatever it takes to provide expert service and advice to anyone who comes into our shop or visits our website.

We started in 1946 as a small shop, helping our neighbors solve trailer and towing problems either over a counter or lying on our backs under their cars in the parking lot. Our goal is to maintain that same level of personal service on the Internet. In passionate pursuit of this goal, we've grown to become the largest online retailer of trailer hitches. With our expert service & awesome products, we make sure the only thing between you & your destination is the road.

description:
The Earth Resources Laboratory (ERL) is MIT’s primary home for research and education focused on sub-surface energy resources. Through integration across disciplines, departments, and school boundaries, and with support from federal agencies and a consortium of energy companies, ERL addresses questions concerning hydrocarbon exploration and production, geothermal energy, CO2 sequestration, and near-surface environments.

ERL’s faculty, research staff, and students work with a variety of methodologies (including geophysical imaging, rock physics and chemistry, multiphase flow, geomechanics, microseismics, and remote sensing) to obtain an understanding of sub-surface reservoirs—their structure, the geological materials of which they are made, the fluids that flow through them, and changes that occur in response to production.

Information about accessibility can be found at https://accessibility.mit.edu/

Welcome to the Advance Driving School YouTube channel! 

We are an independent driving school based in the UK. The videos on our channel suggest ways you can improve your driving, but they are not intended to replace proper driving lessons with an instructor.  Our videos are written to help UK learner drivers perfect the essential driving skills needed to become a safe driver and pass the UK Driving Test. If you are a more experienced driver, or if you live in a different country you may drive in a slightly different way, but we hope you still find our videos interesting.  

Feel free to leave any comments you have about our videos, and if you have a suggestion for the next video we should make please let us know. Please subscribe to our channel, and like your favourite videos as it really helps other people find us. If you would like to help us make videos, then please consider becoming a member of our channel.

Science gets a bad rep for being boring, difficult and for very smart people (see: nerds). But that doesn't have to be the case. At ScienceABC we believe that if science is communicated simply and made relatable and fun, it can be for everyone. As Micheal Jackson said best, "as simple as ABC."

So far, we've tackled complex and vast topics like Einstein's Time Dilation, the Immune System, Evolution, Quantum Entanglement, while also asking the questions that nag us at night like "Is the science in the movies accurate?", "Is it possible to have insects the size of humans?", and "Why can I hear a thundering sound in my ear?"

So, join us for some simple science with a whole lot of fun thrown in! Subscribe to our channel for your weekly dose of science and don't forget to share our work if you liked it.

description: The California High-Speed Rail Authority is responsible for planning, designing, building and operation of the first high-speed rail system in the nation. California high-speed rail will connect the mega-regions of the state, contribute to economic development and a cleaner environment, create jobs and preserve agricultural and protected lands. The system will run from San Francisco to the Los Angeles basin in under three hours at speeds capable of over 200 miles per hour. The system will eventually extend to Sacramento and San Diego, totaling 800 miles with up to 24 stations. In addition, the Authority is working with regional partners to implement a state-wide rail modernization plan that will invest billions of dollars in local and regional rail lines to meet the state's 21st century transportation needs.

Our products have proven their value for more than 15 years, with solid performance in fuel cell research, oil and gas, supercritical, pharmaceutical engineering, green energy and other cutting edge industries.

Since May of 2021, Equilibar has been part of the Richards Industrials Family. Equilibar’s Quality System is ISO 9001:2015 Certified.

We are proud to work and manufacture in the United States and honored to partner with innovators around the world.

Living in the Cosmic World!

This channel tells a story of the strange lights that I have seen since October 2017 in Finland, in region called Osthrobothnia. Finland is a nice country full of pure nature in Northern Europe, in Scandinavia. Without no doubt this phenomenon is very special one and it deserves to be shown also for other people who might be interested in real life; what is happening behind the scene. It also tells us that we are not alone and we have to take attention to our environment and the nature around us. 

Nobody knows how long I will be seeing these cosmic things on the ground or in the sky; it is not up to me! But so far as they will be seen, I will do my best. Welcome to my channel!

description:
(This channel is not affiliated with Hololive and was established November 2006)

When I was young, I got introduced to videogames, but since we were poor and all I had back then (as late as 2006) was a Pentium II (and a Pentium 4 as of 2009), I had to make due with pirated NES multicarts and downloaded SNES ROMS. This spurred me to go retrogaming, and once I was able to record the footage, I had this compulsion to post every playthrough. I generally do a blind run for most games and then rely on the power of rerecording to blaze through it. Since then (and two computer changes; the first to an Athlon 64 X2 and the second to an FX-8320) the upload counts are on the rise and I've been trying to play and chronicle as many games as possible.
